                                                                                                               Ghosh to retire from Vodafone
                          Ghosh: Exit mode                    
	New Delhi, Feb. 6 (PTI): Telecom service provider Vodafone Essar today said its chief executive Asim Ghosh would step down from his post on March 31.        
	However, he would continue to be on the board of Vodafone Essar.         
	Ghosh has been the companys chief executive officer for over 10 years. Marten Pieters, who was earlier the CEO of Celtel International BV, a pan-African mobile operator, will take over from Ghosh.         
	Confirming his retirement, the 61-year old Ghosh said, With Marten, the company will be in great hands.        
	Ghosh joined the company in August 1998 and took over the operations of what is now Vodafone Essar.        
	He started his career in consumer goods marketing with Procter amp; Gamble in the US and Canada.         
	Ghosh moved to Asia in 1989 as co-CEO of Pepsi Foods in India. Thereafter, he held executive positions with Hutchison in Hong Kong and India.                                                                                                                                        
